The paper discusses the security and reliability of the Bitcoin protocol, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI) as it deals with the blockchain and timestamping. The paper also mentions the efficiency and backward compatibility of the proposed protocol, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed systems (cs.DL).
